Key Match Events: David Fry hit a go-ahead, two-run homer in the seventh inning
Beau Brieske pitched scoreless ball for 5 1/3 innings over four postseason appearances
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cleveland ended a streak of 11 losses in postseason elimination games dating to Game 6 of 1997 World Series
Others: Game 5 is Saturday in Cleveland, with ace Tarik Skubal set to start for the Tigers. The winner advances to the ALCS against the New York Yankees starting Monday.
